Neutral DPS, Eective Health, and TDO are computated for Pokmon at level 40, with perfect IVs.
I
Neutral DPS (Damage per Second) represents how much damage a Pokmon can make in a second. It
depends on the Pokmons attack stat (base ATK + ATK IV)0.7903, on the Pokemons fast and charged
moves and on the "Same Type Attack Bonus" (STAB, 25% damage boost of a move when it is the same
type as one of the types of the Pokmon using the move). They dene the damages and the necessary
energy for realising the damages.
DPS12.5 not an attacker
12.5<DPS16 a good attacker (but privilege ATT IV = 15, and level up to 35)
DPS>16 excellent attacker
I
The Eective Health (EH) is computed via the formula:
EH = (base DEF + DEF IV) (base HP + HP IV)
0.7903
2
900
EH25 very fragile
25<EH30 fragile but viable
30<EH35 bulky
EH>35 very bulky
I
TDO (Total Damage Output) represents how much damage a Pokmon can make before it faints. It is
computed via the formula: TDO = DPS EH.
